 literature. The eight essays draw attention to Steel’s multifaceted work—ranging from fiction to journalism to letter writing, from housekeeping manuals to philanthropic activities. These essays, by recognized experts on her life and work, will appeal to interdisciplinary scholars and readers in the fields of British India and Women’s Studies. Contributors: Amrita Banerjee, Helen Pike Bauer, Ralph Crane, Gráinne Goodwin, Alan Johnson, Anna Johnston, Danielle Nielsen, LeeAnne M. Richardson, Susmita Roye  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Indian Literature / Victorian Writing / Colonial Studies.1 aBanerjee, Amrita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Helen Pike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrane, Ralph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodwin, Gráinne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNielsen, Danielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, LeeAnne M, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Leeanne M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoye, Susmita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoye, Susmita, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212324140uhttps://www.degruyte